oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Roster of Co. M, 117th Inf. Regt., 30th Div.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Framed roster of Co. M, 117th Inf. Regt., 30th Div., which belonged to William Clellie Summers (1888-1947). His last name is misspelled on the roster. Roster dates from the unit's return from Europe in 1919. Summers served in Co. M, 117th Inf. Regt., 30th Div. He was Private, 1st Class at time of discharge from service. He was a farmer from Oakdale, Morgan County, Tenn., and he returned to the farm after the war. He died in a hunting accident in 1947.
